            "summary": "Coinbase stock dropped 7% to $244 in after-hours trading on May 15, following news of a cyberattack that exposed customer data and an SEC investigation into misstated user numbers. The SEC has been looking into whether Coinbase misrepresented its user numbers in disclosures, dating back to the Biden administration and continuing under Trump. Coinbase confirmed the investigation and stated it has cooperated with the SEC, pointing out that it no longer reports the metric in question. The SEC took issue with Coinbase's claim of \"100+ million verified users\" in its 2021 marketing and IPO materials, even though the exchange stopped reporting this metric in 2022. Despite the SEC dropping an enforcement lawsuit in 2023, the investigation persists. Additionally, Coinbase experienced a $20 million ransom attempt after being attacked by cybercriminals, leading to data leaks, with expected remediation and reimbursement costs between $180 million to $400 million. Coinbase has hired law firm Davis Polk & Wardwell to aid in its response to the SEC.",
